Curried Shrimp Tacos With Mango Slaw



Serves: 4
PREP TIME: 15 min
COOK TIME: 5 min





Full-page view


Print





























Ingredients

1/2 cup Hellmann’s® or Best Foods® Organic Mild Curry Mayonnaise Dressing

                         
                      1/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro


                        

                         
                      2 Tbsp.  fresh lime juice, divided


                        

                         
                      1 lb.  large uncooked shrimp, peeled and deveined


                        

                         
                      2 cups shredded red cabbage


                        

                         
                      1   mango, julienned
















 


                        

                         
                      1   carrot, julienned 


                        

                         
                      8 (6-in. ea.)  flour tortillas


                        



Directions

Combine Hellmann’s® or Best Foods® Organic Mild Curry Mayonnaise Dressing, cilantro and 1 Tbsp. lime juice in medium bowl. Remove 1 Tbsp. and toss with shrimp in another medium bowl. Remove 1/4 cup and set aside for serving.
Add cabbage, mango and carrot to bowl with remaining dressing; toss and set aside.
Heat large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat and cook shrimp, stirring occasionally, until shrimp turn pink, about 4 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in remaining 1 Tbsp. lime juice.
Place some mango slaw on each tortilla and evenly top with shrimp. Drizzle evenly with reserved curry mixture. Serve remaining mango slaw on the side.


Tip: To speed up prep time, substitute 2-1/2 cups coleslaw mix for cabbage and carrots.


Nutritional Information

Nutritional Information

Nutritional Information


Serving Size
1 serving



