Curry Chicken-Apple Salad



Serves: 4
PREP TIME: 10 min
Marinate for 15 min
COOK TIME: 10 min





Full-page view


Print





























Ingredients


                         
                         CHICKEN:


                        

                         
                      4   boneless, skinless chicken breasts (about 1-1/4 lbs.)


                        
1/4 cup Hellmann’s® or Best Foods® Organic Mild Curry Mayonnaise Dressing

                         
                         SALAD:


                        

                         
                      8 cups  mixed salad greens


                        

                         
                      1   apple, cored and sliced


                        

                         
                      1/2 cup halved red seedless grapes or green seedless grapes


                        

                         
                      1/4 cup slivered red onion


                        

                         
                      1/4 cup chopped toasted walnuts


                        
1/4 cup Hellmann’s® or Best Foods® Organic Mild Curry Mayonnaise Dressing

                         
                      2 tsp.  apple cider vinegar


                        



Directions

For CHICKEN, place chicken on plate; coat with 3 Tbsp. Hellmann’s® or Best Foods® Organic Mild Curry Mayonnaise Dressing. Cover and marinate in refrigerator 15 minutes. Reserve remaining 1 Tbsp. Mayonnaise Dressing.
Heat large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat and cook chicken, turning once, until thoroughly cooked, about 10 minutes, brushing with reserved 1 Tbsp. Mayonnaise Dressing during last minute of cook time.
For SALAD, combine salad greens, apple, grapes, onion and walnuts on serving platter. Slice chicken and place on top. Combine Mayonnaise Dressing with cider vinegar and drizzle over top.




